reviewText: No subtitles for those who want or need them. In fact, not even a menu -  just the play option or previews from the studio selling more of the same cheap productions. If you like cheap wood bead bracelets and necklaces and candles as your props then this movie is for you. Usual plot of Thai mercenaries led by some English speaking white bad guy (Gary Daniels) as they walk into a remote village and start shooting anything that moves while they look for a few females to sell in the sex trade. Danny Trejo in a stereotypic role as a Native or Hispanic with some touching healing powers. He touches a heavily eye scarred woman and the scars disappear; she suddenly sees and her response is "Thank you" in an emotional tone similar to someone thanking the waiter for bringing their order. People die and Trejo brings them back to life with a few dreamy dead walking around in paradise scenes. This other world special effect done by washing out the image.Daniels in his usual stereotypic role as the bad guy as he chases down his stolen prostitution and drugs related money. Would you be surprised that he gets it in the end.
Title: Lazarus Papers

reviewText: I can watch this film over and over for the emotional effect alone.  I feel most are over critical with their reviews.  And commenting on the props without taking them into account with the entire set direction proves they didn't watch the movie for what it was.  The struggle of living a peaceful life without exploitation, genuine love between unsuspecting business partners and vindication for a girl who lost her mother.  Also, the spiritual aspect of this film was a subtle addition to an emotionally touching story.Very Requiem for a Dream meets The Fall.  Two great films.
summary: Requiem for a Dream  meets  The Fall
Title: Lazarus Papers

reviewText: Yes, Danny Trejo usually does the over the top violence movies, guns and blades and chainsaws blazing, but in this film, he brings to life the meaning of life itself, which is love.  The love between people, and the love that can become twisted at times.  But in the end, the movie shows that by allowing real love to live in your heart, even though there is pain and suffering in life, you can truly live.The acting may seem a bit forced, or not quite right, but that was due to trying to cram what lead the people to the places they ended up, and show how ever slightly how they got twisted, or straightened out.I initially watched this movie because it was free with Prime, but after watching it, I then purchased it as well.  It is a truly moving film, and while not everyone will see or understand it, I feel it is well worth seeing and owning.
summary: Too many focused on the usual movies that Danny Trejo does to see the beauty in this film

reviewerName: The Movie Guy "Movies from A to Z"
reviewText: The is nothing like a "bad" Danny Trejo movie. And when I say "bad" I mean "good." Unfortunately this is just a bad Danny Trejo movie with no quotation marks. Danny plays an Eastern holy man/healer who likes flowers. He gets killed in the first scene, but unlike the movie, he doesn't completely die. He can't pass over because there is still work to do, so he occasionally resurrects and helps others along the way.Danny is killed because his peaceful village, where young girls bathe topless in the stream, is raided by Gary Daniels to abduct girls for the sex trade. Meanwhile, John Edward Lee is getting ready to die and has a brief case full of money. He wants a woman. Together Danny and Lee fight against the bad guys (with some police help) to save Nana (Krystal Vee).The film is rather boring. While there is killing, there are not any of the "walking tall" action one would expect in a Trejo film. This is far from a grindhouse, although it makes you think it started out as one. A rather lame role for Trejo in this weak action-drama. The film takes place in Pali, an imaginary Asian city/country near India. Might be an interesting film for Buddhists who are Trejo fans.F-bomb, sexual situations, brief nudity.
Title: Lazarus Papers

reviewText: Watching these movies starring Mr. Trejo and knowing that he prefers to be killed off, this one was quite a surprise. When he gets killed off the first time within about 15 minutes from the start of the movie, I figured that it was yet another "cameo" role for him.  However, I was happy to see that he not only appears many times through out the movie, he gets to be killed off several times!  It centers around Nana and Lonnie, who meet after Nana was kidnapped and held in the sex trade and is HIV positive and makes her escape. Lonnie is literally in his final days of life and neither wants to die alone.  Of course they are the romantic interests in this film.  Sebastian Riker (Gary Daniels) is the arch villain, evil to the core (why are the villains now all from the UK or Australia?), with Bai Ling as the evil and perverted "madam" of the operation who actually is  "Mister" as in the movie "Transamerica" or "The Crying Game". Also, I was quite surprised to see a young man that appeared to be a dead ringer for Forrest Whitaker but without the left-sided micro-opthalmia (a smaller eye).  Turned out it was Damon Whitaker and must be related. He did an excellent job. It has some beautiful settings, and amazing scenery, and the story is very endearing and heart-warming without being too blood-spattering.  This one will go in the "Trejo" collection for multiple watchings. Although this was no "star wars" or "Schindler's List" I believe it deserves a 4 star rating because it was a good story and held my interest.  Also, it proved that no matter how old Mr. Trejo gets, he'll still look good even with gray streaks in his hair and a gray mustache!
summary: This was a really good very well-done movie
Title: Lazarus Papers
